1
00:00:13,144 --> 00:00:16,265
Please let me go.

2
00:00:16,345 --> 00:00:19,025
Please let me go.

3
00:00:19,545 --> 00:00:21,305
Please, please. Let me go. Please.

4
00:00:23,345 --> 00:00:27,505
Let me go. Please don't. Don't.

5
00:00:29,185 --> 00:00:32,305
Don't kill me. No, no, no.

6
00:00:32,385 --> 00:00:34,425
No. Please, don't kill me.

7
00:00:38,985 --> 00:00:42,985
Don't kill me. Please. Please!

8
00:00:43,945 --> 00:00:48,105
No, no, no. No!

9
00:01:53,105 --> 00:01:54,985
- What's going on here?
- Jai Hind, sir.

10
00:01:55,905 --> 00:01:57,465
- Jai Hind, sir.
- Jai Hind, sir.

11
00:01:57,545 --> 00:02:00,105
Is there a criminal here
that you're guarding?

12
00:02:00,185 --> 00:02:01,105
Get moving.

13
00:02:02,145 --> 00:02:04,105
- Out!
- Okay, sir.

14
00:02:07,585 --> 00:02:09,745
- Vincent, Sajjad, Kumar sir is here.
- Okay.

15
00:02:14,185 --> 00:02:15,744
Whose team are you working for?

16
00:02:16,785 --> 00:02:21,185
A custodial death, a potential witness
is killed in a shootout, all in one day?

17
00:02:21,265 --> 00:02:22,185
What is going on?

18
00:02:22,265 --> 00:02:24,185
Sir, I take full responsibility for this.

19
00:02:24,265 --> 00:02:25,145
It is all on you.

20
00:02:28,305 --> 00:02:29,145
And you?

21
00:02:29,985 --> 00:02:32,665
What happened there? Speak up.

22
00:02:34,385 --> 00:02:37,625
Sir… when we reached
Ramesh bhai's house…

23
00:02:48,505 --> 00:02:51,705
Hey! Who are you? How did you get in?

24
00:02:51,785 --> 00:02:53,785
Sir, what are you doing?
The gun could go off.

25
00:02:53,865 --> 00:02:56,305
- I'll kill you. Don't come near.
- Sir, the gun could go off.

26
00:02:56,385 --> 00:02:58,665
- Get back. Get back!
- Sir, you might shoot someone.

27
00:02:58,745 --> 00:03:01,345
Drop the gun, sir. Let go, sir.

28
00:03:02,865 --> 00:03:04,545
Sir? Sir?

29
00:03:07,505 --> 00:03:09,225
Why did you have to play the hero?

30
00:03:10,385 --> 00:03:13,065
The DRI team was already there. Then?

31
00:03:14,345 --> 00:03:16,545
Sir, Commissioner sahib wants to see you.

32
00:03:19,425 --> 00:03:21,265
Who was interrogating Mukim?

33
00:03:23,265 --> 00:03:25,225
Sir, we had exercised full caution.

34
00:03:25,785 --> 00:03:26,945
This is Aslam's doing.

35
00:03:29,785 --> 00:03:31,905
- Send me a detailed report.
- Okay, sir.

36
00:03:31,985 --> 00:03:33,665
Take his statement right now.

37
00:03:37,785 --> 00:03:38,985
Arjun.

38
00:03:47,025 --> 00:03:50,705
- This new guy, what's his name?
- Kulveer Dhuria.

39
00:03:52,225 --> 00:03:55,065
This idiot will get arrested, prosecuted.

40
00:03:55,145 --> 00:03:58,945
Sir, we have to protect him.
I mean, you have to protect him, sir.

41
00:04:02,625 --> 00:04:05,585
- Did you make a DRI-1 of this raid?
- It's on your desk, sir.

42
00:04:29,425 --> 00:04:31,865
Suspend the entire team. Immediately.

43
00:04:34,185 --> 00:04:35,745
- No, sir.
- What?

44
00:04:36,745 --> 00:04:39,345
Just three months
are left for my retirement.

45
00:04:40,385 --> 00:04:41,985
Let me spend my time peacefully!

46
00:04:42,865 --> 00:04:44,665
Do what you want after I've gone.

47
00:04:44,745 --> 00:04:47,065
Not a single member of my team
will be suspended, sir.

48
00:04:48,265 --> 00:04:49,985
I'm transferring them to the back office.

49
00:04:51,185 --> 00:04:53,785
You can initiate
an internal enquiry if you wish.

50
00:04:53,865 --> 00:04:55,385
Allot a six-month time frame.

51
00:04:55,465 --> 00:04:58,145
Because that will be enough for me
to wipe out this syndicate.

52
00:04:58,225 --> 00:04:59,625
Really?

53
00:04:59,705 --> 00:05:01,785
Choudhary has bailed out Aslam.

54
00:05:03,345 --> 00:05:04,705
And Ramesh bhai is dead.

55
00:05:04,785 --> 00:05:06,265
That is my lookout, sir.

56
00:05:07,385 --> 00:05:08,905
My team will not be suspended.

57
00:05:10,665 --> 00:05:14,465
And in return, the way you set me up
in Bangkok will stay within this room.

58
00:05:32,585 --> 00:05:35,465
<i>Rahul almost died because of them,</i>
<i>Choudhary sahib.</i>

59
00:05:35,545 --> 00:05:39,665
<i>Our business runs on fear.</i>
<i>Once fear is gone, business is over.</i>

60
00:05:40,385 --> 00:05:44,225
Listen to me. Take out a couple
and the rest will straighten up.

61
00:05:46,345 --> 00:05:47,185
Rizaura?

62
00:05:47,265 --> 00:05:49,465
<i>Sir, we have taken a big hit.</i>

63
00:05:50,625 --> 00:05:53,585
<i>But I totally disagree</i>
<i>with what Anna is proposing.</i>

64
00:05:54,225 --> 00:05:58,305
<i>We win some and we lose some.</i>
<i>Violence is not a solution.</i>

65
00:05:58,385 --> 00:06:00,105
<i>Hey, what are you talking--</i>

66
00:06:00,185 --> 00:06:01,705
<i>Sorry, but that's what I feel.</i>

67
00:06:04,265 --> 00:06:08,145
I am in agreement with Anna. Let's get rid
of a few guys from their team.

68
00:06:09,745 --> 00:06:11,785
- Junior?
<i>- Yes. boss.</i>

69
00:06:11,865 --> 00:06:13,705
<i>I can't let my couriers suffer.</i>

70
00:06:14,305 --> 00:06:17,665
<i>- If word gets out, then we are done here.</i>
<i>- Totally.</i>

71
00:06:18,265 --> 00:06:19,105
Rahul?

72
00:06:20,705 --> 00:06:22,945
Choudhary sahib,
we have to underline our presence here.

73
00:06:23,025 --> 00:06:26,105
<i>If we don't retaliate,</i>
<i>they'll completely get out of hand.</i>

74
00:06:28,305 --> 00:06:30,145
Sharma <i>ji,</i> call Raghu.

75
00:06:30,225 --> 00:06:31,065
<i>Choudhary sahib.</i>

76
00:06:34,785 --> 00:06:35,985
Yes, Suresh.

77
00:06:36,065 --> 00:06:38,465
<i>There's a middle path.</i>
<i>Want to hear me out?</i>

78
00:07:03,945 --> 00:07:05,105
Hello.

79
00:07:05,185 --> 00:07:07,625
Hello, Arjun Meena. Bada Choudhary here.

80
00:07:19,625 --> 00:07:20,465
Hello?

81
00:07:21,225 --> 00:07:22,105
Relax.

82
00:07:23,105 --> 00:07:24,385
Your heart is racing.

83
00:07:25,705 --> 00:07:27,225
Had I called, it would've been yours.

84
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:29,785
Why did you call?

85
00:07:29,865 --> 00:07:31,825
I have a tip and some advice for you.

86
00:07:33,145 --> 00:07:36,545
The tip is that two of my men
are traveling on EK535 tomorrow,

87
00:07:36,625 --> 00:07:40,025
each carrying 25 kilos of gold
and they will land at your airport.

88
00:07:41,585 --> 00:07:44,585
Their names are
Sushil Verma and Atul Rathod.

89
00:07:46,025 --> 00:07:48,865
And my advice is that you won't stop them.

90
00:07:49,505 --> 00:07:51,305
Rather, you'll let them exit safely.

91
00:07:51,385 --> 00:07:53,665
Why would I take your advice, Choudhary?

92
00:07:55,705 --> 00:07:59,705
Because one should listen to elders,
Arjun. It's part of our culture.

93
00:08:10,465 --> 00:08:12,025
- Mom?
- Yes?

94
00:08:12,105 --> 00:08:15,585
- I'm going to win at the Sports Day.
- Okay.

95
00:08:15,665 --> 00:08:18,585
I run so fast
that everyone will be stunned.

96
00:08:25,105 --> 00:08:25,945
Hand it over.

97
00:08:29,705 --> 00:08:30,545
Let's go.

98
00:08:40,065 --> 00:08:42,705
- Shall I show you how I run?
- Yes, okay.

99
00:08:46,465 --> 00:08:50,345
Mom. Mom! Mom, I won! I won!

100
00:08:50,425 --> 00:08:52,345
- Mitali madam!
- Yes?

101
00:08:52,425 --> 00:08:54,545
A small gift for you from Choudhary sahib.

102
00:08:57,265 --> 00:08:59,385
- Jiya!
- Oh, no!

103
00:08:59,465 --> 00:09:00,625
- Mom!
- Jiya!

104
00:09:00,705 --> 00:09:01,665
Momma, I can't see.

105
00:09:16,945 --> 00:09:18,425
Give me the gun.

106
00:09:30,545 --> 00:09:31,625
How are you, sahib?

107
00:09:34,145 --> 00:09:36,705
What, sahib? You seize a lot of our stuff.

108
00:09:37,425 --> 00:09:39,425
Stop bringing it in, I'll stop seizing.

109
00:09:40,385 --> 00:09:43,665
You'll land in a big mess someday.
Use your brain a little.

110
00:09:46,505 --> 00:09:47,345
Got it?

111
00:09:49,025 --> 00:09:51,185
A petty goon like you
will explain it to me?

112
00:09:52,225 --> 00:09:53,905
You're a big gangster now?

113
00:10:00,905 --> 00:10:03,385
Choudhary sahib
has sent a special gift for you.

114
00:11:00,545 --> 00:11:01,745
What happened?

115
00:11:05,505 --> 00:11:07,905
<i>Mom! Mom! I won! I won!</i>

116
00:11:07,985 --> 00:11:09,465
<i>A gift from Choudhary sahib.</i>

117
00:11:11,745 --> 00:11:14,305
<i>- Mom! Mom!</i>
<i>- Jiya!</i>

118
00:11:16,185 --> 00:11:17,705
- Mom!
- Jiya!

119
00:11:17,785 --> 00:11:20,065
- Nothing happened. Nothing happened.
- Mom!

120
00:11:20,145 --> 00:11:22,065
- Just a second. Just a second.
- Madam!

121
00:11:22,145 --> 00:11:24,305
It was just chili water this time.

122
00:11:24,385 --> 00:11:27,145
Mend your ways.
Or it'll be acid next time. Let's go.

123
00:11:29,505 --> 00:11:31,185
Baby, listen to me.

124
00:11:31,265 --> 00:11:33,345
Look at me, baby. Look at me.

125
00:11:33,425 --> 00:11:35,265
Nothing happened. It was just water.

126
00:11:35,345 --> 00:11:36,305
Are you okay?

127
00:11:37,425 --> 00:11:39,585
A special gift for you
from Choudhary sahib.

128
00:11:47,905 --> 00:11:49,945
How did you like our demo, Gujjar sahib?

129
00:11:50,745 --> 00:11:56,105
It'll be real bullets next time.
Mend your ways. Asshole!

130
00:12:01,425 --> 00:12:03,865
And they all got calls too. Vincent?

131
00:12:07,025 --> 00:12:09,585
They described
my dad's entire routine with timings.

132
00:12:10,385 --> 00:12:13,105
They've warned me
that if I try to be too duty-driven…

133
00:12:14,025 --> 00:12:15,745
In front of the church, my dad will be…

134
00:12:16,585 --> 00:12:17,705
They called me too and said

135
00:12:17,785 --> 00:12:20,905
that the blue shirt
was better than the one I wore today.

136
00:12:21,865 --> 00:12:23,185
They've threatened me too.

137
00:12:24,145 --> 00:12:26,225
Not to get swayed by seniors.

138
00:12:26,305 --> 00:12:30,065
I got a threat call on the landline, sir.
By chance, my wife picked it up.

139
00:12:30,825 --> 00:12:33,665
She is still howling.

140
00:12:33,745 --> 00:12:34,985
She hasn't stopped, sir.

141
00:12:35,865 --> 00:12:36,705
Sir!

142
00:12:38,145 --> 00:12:39,985
I was walking on the car, sir.

143
00:12:40,665 --> 00:12:43,265
And a red colored road swerved past me.

144
00:12:53,305 --> 00:12:55,985
- Hello?
<i>- We spared you this time, bloody Sajjad!</i>

145
00:12:56,545 --> 00:12:59,425
<i>If you stop Choudhary sahib's courier</i>
<i>ever at the airport,</i>

146
00:12:59,505 --> 00:13:02,425
<i>we'll run you over with this car. Got it?</i>

147
00:13:02,505 --> 00:13:04,625
I have two little kids, sir.

148
00:13:05,825 --> 00:13:07,785
Vincent, take Sajjad.

149
00:13:07,865 --> 00:13:09,705
- Get him changed. Come on.
- Sir.

150
00:13:10,665 --> 00:13:11,505
Let's go.

151
00:13:11,585 --> 00:13:14,065
If I wanted to be shot,
I'd have joined the army, man.

152
00:13:14,145 --> 00:13:16,305
Relax. Relax. Come on.

153
00:13:21,385 --> 00:13:23,025
- Mitali.
- Yes, sir?

154
00:13:24,105 --> 00:13:25,705
You want to take Jiya for counseling?

155
00:13:30,785 --> 00:13:35,145
No need, sir.
She is a tough kid. She'll handle it.

156
00:13:36,945 --> 00:13:39,305
Sir, since everybody is here, so…

157
00:13:40,785 --> 00:13:42,185
I have a recording.

158
00:13:45,865 --> 00:13:47,745
<i>I have a tip and some advice for you.</i>

159
00:13:48,345 --> 00:13:52,225
<i>The tip is that two of my men</i>
<i>are traveling on EK535 tomorrow,</i>

160
00:13:52,305 --> 00:13:55,665
<i>each carrying 25 kilos of gold</i>
<i>and they will land at your airport.</i>

161
00:13:55,745 --> 00:13:58,665
<i>Their names are</i>
<i>Sushil Verma and Atul Rathod.</i>

162
00:13:59,545 --> 00:14:02,025
<i>And the advice is that</i>
<i>you won't stop them.</i>

163
00:14:03,025 --> 00:14:04,985
<i>Rather, you will let them exit safely.</i>

164
00:14:06,345 --> 00:14:08,105
It's about to land in half an hour.

165
00:14:08,185 --> 00:14:10,305
I'll catch them both
and take them to the police--

166
00:14:10,385 --> 00:14:11,945
Gujjar, don't be stupid.

167
00:14:12,785 --> 00:14:15,665
- It's not just about you.
- Thank… Thank you, sir.

168
00:14:16,865 --> 00:14:19,665
No, I mean I am grateful
that you think like this.

169
00:14:21,465 --> 00:14:22,745
- He is right.
- Arjun.

170
00:14:25,825 --> 00:14:27,665
Sir, we should let them go today.

171
00:14:27,745 --> 00:14:29,545
Today Choudhary has the upper hand.

172
00:14:30,465 --> 00:14:32,265
We are not ready for today's war.

173
00:14:33,425 --> 00:14:35,065
Let's live to fight another day.

174
00:14:36,585 --> 00:14:37,425
Agreed.

175
00:14:39,705 --> 00:14:40,985
Let's lie low today.

176
00:14:42,945 --> 00:14:45,225
Let Choudhary
have the delusion of a victory.

177
00:15:14,905 --> 00:15:15,985
Look, there he is.

178
00:15:23,945 --> 00:15:25,665
He is not going to do anything.

179
00:15:31,745 --> 00:15:32,585
No, he knows it.

180
00:15:38,425 --> 00:15:40,585
Let's drop the bag and get going.

181
00:15:42,865 --> 00:15:44,865
Come on, bhai. Put it on the belt quick.

182
00:15:45,745 --> 00:15:48,905
Did you see their faces?
They were scared to the bone.

183
00:15:48,985 --> 00:15:51,985
Choudhary sir's terror is such, bhai.
They have to be scared.

184
00:15:57,505 --> 00:16:00,625
Hurry up, man. Give the bag. Give it.

185
00:16:24,985 --> 00:16:26,225
They're just taking it all in.

186
00:16:26,305 --> 00:16:27,585
None could've stopped us.

187
00:16:31,145 --> 00:16:32,265
Grab the bag.

188
00:16:35,025 --> 00:16:35,985
Bloody hell!

189
00:16:39,265 --> 00:16:40,785
You fucker!

190
00:16:44,465 --> 00:16:46,145
Get him! Hold him!

191
00:16:51,265 --> 00:16:52,545
Let go!

192
00:17:11,944 --> 00:17:12,944
Come on.

193
00:17:13,025 --> 00:17:14,865
Take a good look at these smugglers!

194
00:17:15,665 --> 00:17:17,785
They were bringing gold into India.

195
00:17:19,665 --> 00:17:21,665
This will be the fate of every smuggler.

196
00:17:21,745 --> 00:17:23,665
- Move!
- Wow!

197
00:17:37,785 --> 00:17:39,625
This is called integrity.

198
00:17:39,705 --> 00:17:43,265
No government officer
has the guts to do this nowadays.

199
00:17:50,865 --> 00:17:53,105
<i>They were bringing gold into India.</i>

200
00:17:54,945 --> 00:17:56,945
<i>This will be the fate of every smuggler.</i>

201
00:17:57,025 --> 00:17:57,865
<i>Move!</i>

202
00:17:59,225 --> 00:18:00,065
<i>Move!</i>

203
00:18:09,025 --> 00:18:10,825
Ranjeet, it's Arbab.

204
00:18:17,985 --> 00:18:19,225
<i>Salaam alaikum,</i> Arbab.

205
00:18:19,305 --> 00:18:20,665
<i>Waliakum-asalaam.</i>

206
00:18:21,625 --> 00:18:24,705
Fifty kilos of gold was seized
again yesterday, Choudhary sahib.

207
00:18:26,705 --> 00:18:28,025
I was sure it would go through.

208
00:18:28,105 --> 00:18:30,105
But it didn't.

209
00:18:31,265 --> 00:18:33,665
Omar sahib wants to see you
as soon as possible.

210
00:18:33,745 --> 00:18:34,985
I'll get back to you.

211
00:18:35,065 --> 00:18:36,785
You didn't get me.

212
00:18:38,185 --> 00:18:41,465
Omar sahib wants
to meet you here at the earliest.

213
00:18:46,345 --> 00:18:47,585
I'll take the morning flight.

214
00:18:47,665 --> 00:18:48,785
Thank you.

215
00:19:13,025 --> 00:19:15,865
- Sorry, man.
- Don't mess with me.

216
00:19:16,825 --> 00:19:18,265
I had told you to control yourself.

217
00:19:19,145 --> 00:19:20,665
Let go today, grab them tomorrow.

218
00:19:22,145 --> 00:19:24,105
Now we all are on Choudhary's radar.

219
00:19:24,185 --> 00:19:27,065
You shouldn't have interfered.
I was handling it.

220
00:19:27,145 --> 00:19:30,585
Hey, Iron Man! Had I not been there,
he would have beaten the hell out of you.

221
00:19:30,665 --> 00:19:32,065
Beaten the hell, my foot!

222
00:19:41,385 --> 00:19:43,105
What is it now? Why are you crying?

223
00:19:43,825 --> 00:19:44,825
Nothing.

224
00:19:51,345 --> 00:19:52,905
Will you just tell me what's wrong?

225
00:19:54,505 --> 00:19:56,465
I got a call from dad today.

226
00:20:00,785 --> 00:20:01,705
He'd seen the video.

227
00:20:03,225 --> 00:20:04,545
You know what he said?

228
00:20:07,105 --> 00:20:10,385
He called me a complete idiot.

229
00:20:16,945 --> 00:20:19,745
My own father calls me an idiot

230
00:20:21,145 --> 00:20:23,065
because I didn't sell my integrity.

231
00:20:26,105 --> 00:20:27,785
What a bullshit world this is!

232
00:20:29,905 --> 00:20:31,385
What kind of father,

233
00:20:33,705 --> 00:20:35,785
what kind of family, what kind of society,

234
00:20:37,345 --> 00:20:40,945
calls an honest person an idiot?

235
00:20:42,385 --> 00:20:43,225
You know…

236
00:20:43,305 --> 00:20:45,265
This is a weak society, Gujjar.

237
00:20:47,105 --> 00:20:50,665
Honest people like you
are in the minority in this society.

238
00:20:51,745 --> 00:20:52,665
That's why.

239
00:20:55,665 --> 00:20:56,785
I'm proud of you guys.

240
00:20:59,385 --> 00:21:00,385
Never change.

241
00:21:02,505 --> 00:21:05,425
You are setting an example
for generations to come.

242
00:21:06,545 --> 00:21:10,545
So, always trust yourself
and your attitude.

243
00:21:12,065 --> 00:21:13,105
It's okay.

244
00:21:14,025 --> 00:21:14,985
Thank you, sir.

245
00:21:18,625 --> 00:21:20,105
But the video has gone viral.

246
00:21:22,025 --> 00:21:22,945
All the way to Delhi.

247
00:21:45,905 --> 00:21:47,985
Here we are, your home sweet home.

248
00:21:55,945 --> 00:21:56,785
Listen.

249
00:21:57,385 --> 00:21:59,105
It's your turn to pick me up tomorrow.

250
00:21:59,745 --> 00:22:00,985
Will do.

251
00:22:02,305 --> 00:22:03,145
See you.

252
00:22:45,145 --> 00:22:46,785
I called off my engagement.

253
00:22:50,105 --> 00:22:50,945
Why?

254
00:22:52,065 --> 00:22:53,745
Did he turn out to be honest too?

255
00:23:00,665 --> 00:23:01,865
No.

256
00:23:04,465 --> 00:23:08,225
He's corrupt and that's what
he'll be his entire life.

257
00:23:15,185 --> 00:23:18,145
I saw you thrashing those smugglers today,

258
00:23:20,585 --> 00:23:25,745
I realized both the value
and significance of integrity.

259
00:23:35,425 --> 00:23:38,345
I won't be able to afford
your dream lifestyle, Meenakshi.

260
00:23:42,785 --> 00:23:45,265
I am human, Ravi.

261
00:23:45,905 --> 00:23:46,945
I'm sorry.

262
00:23:52,265 --> 00:23:54,225
I shared everything with you.

263
00:23:55,905 --> 00:24:00,105
- Personal, professional, and--
- I'm really sorry.

264
00:24:08,385 --> 00:24:10,865
- Let's go home.
- No.

265
00:24:15,985 --> 00:24:17,905
I don't deserve you.

266
00:24:22,225 --> 00:24:24,345
Don't sit here. Come on.

267
00:24:26,225 --> 00:24:27,625
I will come.

268
00:24:30,545 --> 00:24:33,665
I will come back to you the day

269
00:24:33,745 --> 00:24:35,185
you forgive me completely.

270
00:24:39,825 --> 00:24:41,545
I really love you, Ravi.

271
00:24:58,225 --> 00:25:00,785
You never took so long to answer.

272
00:25:09,985 --> 00:25:10,865
It's okay.

273
00:26:12,865 --> 00:26:13,705
Hello?

274
00:26:13,785 --> 00:26:15,345
Arjun Meena.

275
00:26:16,145 --> 00:26:18,185
I gave you some advice yesterday.

276
00:26:18,265 --> 00:26:21,105
I didn't like your advice, Choudhary.
So I didn't take it.

277
00:26:21,185 --> 00:26:22,905
I know. So listen to this now.

278
00:26:26,985 --> 00:26:29,825
If they're ringing my doorbell,
tell your men to wait there.

279
00:26:29,905 --> 00:26:30,945
I'm coming upstairs.

280
00:26:31,025 --> 00:26:34,825
<i>The doorbell is being rung</i>
<i>at Apartment 2/56, Seva Sadan.</i>

281
00:26:35,585 --> 00:26:39,105
And you very well know
who lives at that address.

282
00:27:10,185 --> 00:27:13,385
Let go, fucker! Let go!

283
00:28:30,105 --> 00:28:31,505
Hey! Hey!

284
00:28:33,705 --> 00:28:36,185
Gujjar! Gujjar!

285
00:28:37,305 --> 00:28:38,505
Gujjar!

286
00:30:26,145 --> 00:30:29,905
Please send the raid profile
by the evening to sir and me.

287
00:30:29,985 --> 00:30:30,825
Sir.

288
00:30:32,065 --> 00:30:33,345
Search warrant, sir.

289
00:30:36,345 --> 00:30:38,305
- Yeah. You can start.
- Okay, get going.

290
00:30:40,705 --> 00:30:42,665
It's a search warrant for the house.

291
00:30:44,025 --> 00:30:45,345
Yeah. For the house.

292
00:31:22,705 --> 00:31:23,585
Let's go.

293
00:31:33,425 --> 00:31:35,425
They found 50 lakhs
in cash in the kitchen.

294
00:31:38,865 --> 00:31:40,505
We both know what's happening.

295
00:31:46,345 --> 00:31:47,785
- Chouhan?
- Yes, sir.

296
00:31:48,945 --> 00:31:50,545
- Did you inform the family?
- Yes.

297
00:32:20,065 --> 00:32:21,225
My child.

298
00:32:21,305 --> 00:32:23,505
What happened to Ravinder?

299
00:32:24,585 --> 00:32:26,985
He was fine. What happened?

300
00:32:30,185 --> 00:32:32,105
Come on. I need a ride.

301
00:32:45,145 --> 00:32:46,945
- Take a left ahead.
- Okay, sir.

302
00:32:54,705 --> 00:32:56,505
Right into that compound.

303
00:33:10,545 --> 00:33:11,465
Get down.

304
00:33:14,505 --> 00:33:15,865
Why are we here, sir?

305
00:33:17,265 --> 00:33:19,785
- How much did you get for killing Ramesh?
- Sir?

306
00:33:21,305 --> 00:33:22,745
- Sir?
- Hey?

307
00:33:22,825 --> 00:33:24,465
- Speak up!
- What's happening?

308
00:33:24,545 --> 00:33:26,865
One crore, sir. Sir, please listen to me.

309
00:33:26,945 --> 00:33:28,625
- Who are you?
- Superintendent Arjun Meena.

310
00:33:28,705 --> 00:33:30,145
Where is the Senior PI's cabin?

311
00:33:30,225 --> 00:33:31,145
- This way.
- Move.

312
00:33:31,225 --> 00:33:32,145
Please listen to me.

313
00:33:32,225 --> 00:33:34,745
Please, sir.
Please listen to me once, sir.

314
00:33:36,185 --> 00:33:37,025
Come in.

315
00:33:37,105 --> 00:33:39,305
Please listen to me once, sir.

316
00:33:39,385 --> 00:33:41,865
Superintendent Arjun Meena
from Mumbai Customs, sir.

317
00:33:41,945 --> 00:33:44,585
This kid wants to give a confession.

318
00:33:46,745 --> 00:33:47,905
- Sit down.
- Sir.

319
00:33:47,985 --> 00:33:49,945
And start talking. Come on!

320
00:33:56,225 --> 00:33:59,225
I got a call an hour before

321
00:33:59,305 --> 00:34:01,745
<i>we were to leave for the raid.</i>

322
00:34:05,705 --> 00:34:06,545
Hello?

323
00:34:06,625 --> 00:34:08,105
Just answer in yes or no.

324
00:34:08,825 --> 00:34:10,025
Do you want to earn one crore?

325
00:34:19,985 --> 00:34:22,344
Our man will meet you
at the Starbucks outside.

326
00:34:22,425 --> 00:34:25,425
He will give you 50 lakh rupees and a gun.

327
00:34:25,505 --> 00:34:30,145
<i>Your team is going to raid</i>
<i>Ramesh bhai's house at 10:30 am sharp.</i>

328
00:34:30,225 --> 00:34:35,025
But you won't find Ramesh bhai there.
There is a prayer room in his house.

329
00:34:35,105 --> 00:34:37,665
<i>A sculpture is hung</i>
<i>on the wall of that room.</i>

330
00:34:38,545 --> 00:34:41,705
There is a cavity room behind that idol.

331
00:34:42,505 --> 00:34:44,585
That's where you'll find Ramesh bhai.

332
00:34:45,385 --> 00:34:46,824
Kill him.

333
00:34:47,505 --> 00:34:50,465
The remaining 50 lakhs
will be at your home in the evening.

334
00:34:58,264 --> 00:34:59,824
There's nothing here. Come on.

335
00:35:23,345 --> 00:35:25,385
Who the hell are you? How'd you get in?

336
00:35:25,465 --> 00:35:27,665
I've been sent for your safety,
Ramesh bhai.

337
00:35:27,745 --> 00:35:29,385
Please sit, I'll check.

338
00:35:32,065 --> 00:35:34,025
Please sit, sir. I'm here.

339
00:35:46,505 --> 00:35:48,585
Hey! What's that?

340
00:35:49,505 --> 00:35:50,465
You bloody--

341
00:36:03,425 --> 00:36:05,065
Sir! Sir!

342
00:36:05,145 --> 00:36:08,305
You killed a man for money? Bastard!

343
00:36:11,185 --> 00:36:14,665
He was a criminal, sir.
An enemy of the nation and society.

344
00:36:15,505 --> 00:36:18,065
I was getting one crore, so I did it, sir.

345
00:36:18,945 --> 00:36:23,545
It was a mistake, sir. Please forgive me.

346
00:36:23,625 --> 00:36:24,905
- Constable!
- Forgive me.

347
00:36:27,865 --> 00:36:31,465
It was a mistake. Please forgive me ,sir.

348
00:36:34,585 --> 00:36:36,585
Sir, forgive me. Sir.

349
00:36:38,225 --> 00:36:39,985
Arjun, I'm a little confused.

350
00:36:41,105 --> 00:36:43,065
You are at the Gamdevi police station.

351
00:36:43,825 --> 00:36:46,665
<i>And my men are just leaving.</i>

352
00:36:46,745 --> 00:36:49,305
Priya is in one of your safe houses,

353
00:36:49,945 --> 00:36:52,145
so in this insane Mumbai traffic,

354
00:36:53,265 --> 00:36:55,105
who will get to her faster?

355
00:36:57,705 --> 00:37:01,305
You… or my men?

356
00:41:22,945 --> 00:41:27,945
Subtitle translation by: Monika Saraf
